, \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_F._Kennedy\"}, {\"begin\": 338, \"end\": 347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9927721827470498, \"rank\": 0.006884809917211153, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kennedy, 27, earned $104,400 after securing gold in the women's pole vault marking her as the first Australian woman to achieve this at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 350, \"to\": 499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 350, \"end\": 357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_F._Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.9998481168839278, \"rank\": 0.0001386165966602245, \"text\": \"Kennedy\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_F._Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_F._Kennedy\"}, {\"begin\": 450, \"end\": 460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.7754995116231912, \"rank\": 0.2892059445725132, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The national pole vault record holder's golden payout was due to her win in the athletes category meaning she received an additional $74,000 from the World Athletics Committee.\", \"from\": 501, \"to\": 677, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 651, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9997632405997452, \"rank\": 0.00023681546852060597, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia's performance in Paris was strong, with 18 gold medals across various sports, making it the country's most successful Olympics ever.\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 821, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 679, \"end\": 688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9927721827470498, \"rank\": 0.006884809917211153, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 706, \"end\": 711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999506374037, \"rank\": 4.936267840407981e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Australian and New Zealand athletes are only eligible for one payment based on their best result.\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 929, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 832, \"end\": 842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.7754995116231912, \"rank\": 0.2892059445725132, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 847, \"end\": 858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.42220111777251895, \"rank\": 0.675894270037837, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New Zealand's Hamish Kerr was the highest-earning medallist from his country after securing a gold medal in the men's high jump.\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 1059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 931, \"end\": 942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.42220111777251895, \"rank\": 0.675894270037837, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Kerr\", \"score\": 0.9999998928324261, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hamish Kerr\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Kerr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Kerr\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, two Hong Kong fencing athletes emerged as the highest earners of the Olympics, each winning $1,169,728 despite taking home just one gold medal.\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1215, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1076, \"end\": 1085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"score\": 0.9138539689096647, \"rank\": 0.09113004983577808, \"text\": \"Hong Kong\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The mammoth incentive was thanks to Hong Kong's cash reward which has increased by 20 per cent since the Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 1217, \"to\": 1337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1253, \"end\": 1262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"score\": 0.9138539689096647, \"rank\": 0.09113004983577808, \"text\": \"Hong Kong\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In comparison, China's Yufei Zhang, who claimed the most medals at the Games with six, earned only $342,000.\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1354, \"end\": 1359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.997778775067097, \"rank\": 0.002178306637465727, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\